{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab25fc5a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8451a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8451a"},"text":"§ 8451a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Superintendent","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab25fc5b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8451a/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" There is a Superintendent of the United States Naval Academy. The immediate governance of the Naval Academy is under the Superintendent.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab25fc5c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8451a/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Superintendent shall be detailed to that position by the President. As a condition for detail to that position, an officer shall acknowledge that upon termination of that detail the officer shall be retired pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8371/a"},"text":"section 8371(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":", unless such retirement is waived under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8371/b"},"text":"section 8371(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab25fc5d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8451a/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An officer who is detailed to the position of Superintendent shall be so detailed for a period of not less than three years. In any case in which an officer serving as Superintendent is reassigned or retires before having completed three years service as Superintendent, or otherwise leaves that position (other than due to death) without having completed three years service in that position, the Secretary of the Navy shall submit to Congress notice that such officer left the position of Superintendent without having completed three years service in that position, together with a statement of the reasons why that officer did not complete three years service in that position.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab25fc5e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/65/dA/tV/s532/a/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–65, div. A, title V, § 532(a)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/603"},"text":"113 Stat. 603","children":[],"tail":", § 6951a; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/dA/tV/s541/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, div. A, title V, § 541(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1903"},"text":"118 Stat. 1903","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 8451a and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 807(c)(1), 809(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1836"},"text":"132 Stat. 1836","children":[],"tail":", 1840.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab25fc5f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab25fc60-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab25fc61-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s807/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 807(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s6951a"},"text":"section 6951a of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s809/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 809(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 8371(a)” for “section 6371(a)” and “section 8371(b)” for “section 6371(b)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/s541/b/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, § 541(b)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted before period at end “pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s6371/a"},"text":"section 6371(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":", unless such retirement is waived under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s6371/b"},"text":"section 6371(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/s541/b/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, § 541(b)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idab25fc62-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab25fc63-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2018 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-02-01"},"text":"Feb. 1, 2019","children":[],"tail":", with provision for the coordination of amendments and special rule for certain redesignations, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s800"},"text":"section 800 of Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idab25fc64-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Application of Section to Superintendents Serving on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-05"},"text":"October 5, 1999","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section not applicable to an officer serving on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1999","children":[],"tail":", in the position of Superintendent of the United States Military Academy, Naval Academy, or Air Force Academy for so long as that officer continues on and after that date to serve in that position without a break in service, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/65/s532/a/5"},"text":"section 532(a)(5) of Pub. L. 106–65","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s7321"},"text":"section 7321 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
